! Map Shift+{AltGr / Right Alt} to the Compose key (for typing accents etc.)
! See:
! - https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Xmodmap#Compose_key
! - https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compose_key
! - https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Xorg/Keyboard_configuration#Configuring_compose_key
! Each column on the RHS corresponds to a combination of modifier keys:
! 1. Key
! 2. Shift+Key
! 3. Mode_switch+Key
! 4. Mode_switch+Shift+Key
! 5. ISO_Level3_Shift+Key
! 6. ISO_Level3_Shift+Shift+Key
! Usage:
! Press Shift+Right Alt, then press a compose sequence. Examples:
! - Compose, ', e -> é
! - Compose, =, e -> €
! - Compose, ?, ? -> ¿
! - All in: /usr/share/X11/locale/en_US.UTF-8/Compose (search for <Multi_key>)
keycode 108 = Alt_R Multi_key Meta_R Alt_R Meta_R
